<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-26T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-26T07:00:00-05:00" n="919" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25076:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-26T15:00:00+03:00">October 26, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 26—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>933. Department’s 535, and 537 of October 24 arrived only today. I
                            presented the matter to Lozovski<note n="7" xml:id="d919fn7">S. A.
                                Lozovsky, Assistant People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the
                                Soviet Union.</note> this afternoon who hopes to have a reply for me
                            tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>